camel=second word first letter should be capital 
-> arrayName.length 
snake case means with underscore 
-> string_name.length()
  -> in java it is preffered to use camel case to write production level code 
ex: void additionOfTwoNumbers(){
}


type of printin formats :

->format 1
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
     int[] arr={1,2,3,4,5};
     for(int i=0;i<arr.length;i++){
       System.out.println(arr[i] + " ");
     }
  }
}


you can print array values using simple for loops 


->format 2 
  you can print array values using foreach() loops 

for(int i:arr){
System.out.print(i+ "  ");
}
-> in for each loop we dont need inde values 




-> format 3
import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
     int[] arr={1,2,3,4,5};
    
       System.out.println(Arrays.toString(arr));
     
  }
}


->toString is an inbuilt method to print an array 
->toString can accept only one argument that is array only  ,if we want to store sec argument it will show error


//declaring size of an array and initializing the values later 
->array having fixed size if we declare an array size it cant be changed 

int[] arr=new int[5];
int[] arr is array of reference object created  reference and new is object created in heap memory 
for that particular data type and size '
->if the array type   is integer the default value is 0.
->if it is a string the default values are null and null is a literal 


import java.util.*;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
     Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
     int[] arr=new int[5];
     System.out.println("enter the values");
    // arr[0]=1; 
    // arr[1]=2;
    // arr[2]=3;
    // arr[3]=4;
    // arr[4]=5;
    for(int i=0;i<arr.length;i++){
      arr[i]=sc.nextInt();
    }
    for(int i=0;i<arr.length;i++){
      System.out.println(arr[i]);
    }
    // for(int i:arr){
    //   System.out.print(i);
    // }
    System.out.print(Arrays.toString(arr));
    
     
  }
}

->whenever you are trying to assign or tryig to get nth value of array , u will gwt exception called array out of bound 





